Aim for 20-25 and submit to cap your score at 0 if things go south!

message: Focus on the 'growth serum'. Its first use on an ingredient creates a 'grown' item with a positive value (5-15). Combine 'grown' items from different habitats (land, water, air) to create higher value hybrids (e.g., grown land + grown water = 25-35). Applying 'growth serum' a second time to a 'grown' item makes it 'super-grown', which often increases value (e.g., 5 -> 10, 10 -> 20, 20 -> 30). However, be extremely cautious with large or already combined 'grown' items on the second application, as it can sometimes drastically reduce value (e.g., 30 -> 5). Crucially, avoid applying 'growth serum' a third time, as 'ultra-grown' items almost always have negative values. The 'mutation catalyst' consistently produced negative values in my experience, so avoid it unless you discover a specific positive interaction. Submit when you have a high-value item and further actions are risky.

message: Hello! The 'growth serum' (ğŸŒ¡ï¸) is your best friend. Use it on all base ingredients to make them 'grown' (small: 5, medium: 10, large: 15). Combine two 'grown' items, especially from different habitats, for a good boost (e.g., 20-25). Then, use the 'growth serum' again on these combined items to make them 'super-grown' (e.g., 30-35). Combining 2-3 'super-grown' items from different habitats often yields the highest values (45-50).
